com.example.trialio.controllers

Class UserManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.trialio.controllers.UserManager

  • public class UserManager
extends java.lang.Object
    UserManager manages Users in the system and is responsible for the persistence of User data. This class is used to perform create, read, update and delete functionality on Users which are to be maintained by the system. This class communicates with the Firebase database where User data is maintained.

                                                                       java.lang.String id)
        Creates a new User in the system.

        Note that this User object will not track changes to the User document. If you need to receive all database updates for the User, fetch the User using UserManager#addUserUpdateListener()

        Parameters:
        user - the new User object to be added to the system
        id - the id of new User to create in the system
        Returns:
        Task that indicates when the user has been created

      • getUserById

        public void getUserById(java.lang.String id,
                        UserManager.OnUserFetchListener listener)
        Gets a User from the database by the user id. If a user with the given id is found, the User object is passed into the given callback listener. If a User with the given id does not exist in the system, NULL is passed into the callback.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the User to retrieve
        listener - the callback to be called when the User is fetched

      • addUserUpdateListener

        public void addUserUpdateListener(java.lang.String username,
                                  UserManager.OnUserFetchListener listener)
        Add a listener to a User document that will listen for updates to the User data. This method is used to fetch User data from the database and continue to fetch real-time data for a User. 
         UserManager manager = new UserManager();
 manager.addUserUpdateListener(userId, new UserManager.OnUserUpdateListener() {
     @Override
     public void onUserUpdate(User user) {
         // Do something with the User every time the database is updated
     }
 });
        Parameters:
        username - the username of the User to be fetched
        listener - the listener to be called when the User document is fetched

      • transferUsername

        public com.google.android.gms.tasks.Task<java.lang.Void> transferUsername(User user,
                                                                          java.lang.String newUsername)
        Transfers a User profile to a new username. If the username is not available, the process fails and the failure response can be captured with a onFailure listener to the returned Task. If the username is available and the switch is performed, the sucsess response can be captured with a onSuccess listener to the returned tasks
        Parameters:

        newUsername - the new username to transfer the user profile
        Returns:
